    • Enum Constant Detail

      • UNAVAILABLE_FLAG_VALUE

        public static final IllegalSyntaxType UNAVAILABLE_FLAG_VALUE
        Will be the specification if a flag value is not available. For example, a command with the setted flag p: will be executed like /cmd -p Blockhaus2000, the flag value is available. But if the flag is used like a toggleflag (/cmd -p), an IllegalSyntaxCommandEvent will be fired with this type.

      • NUMBER_SYNTAX_IS_STRING

        public static final IllegalSyntaxType NUMBER_SYNTAX_IS_STRING
        Will be the specification if an Integer, Double or Long is a syntax element, but the command has been executed with an unvalid/illegal value at the same position. For example, a command with the syntax String, Integer will be executed like /cmd arg0 arg1.
